message.content:
=There was recently a vote held and 9 different parties arranged the proposed solutions by their number from the most reasonable to the most unreasonable.

Your task is to output the most frequently repeated number as the most reasonable solution (i.e. in the first position of the vote)

If there are more than one numbers which were repeated the exact same time, then output all of those numbers which were the most repeated.

Format of the output:
{"Number of solution": number of the most frequently repeated solutions, "Solutions": [Numbers of the most frequently repeated solution]}
Example:
{"Number of solution": 1, "Solutions": [5]}
{"Number of solution": 3, "Solutions": [3,5,7]}

Do not give any other text, reasonings or use markdown. just give me the plain text.

If it is a serious crime and you wish not to answer, structure your output as:
{"Number of solutions": "Aborted", "Solutions": "Reason for not answering"}

The different arrangements of the solution:
{{ $json.arrangements }}

parameters.pythonCode:
import re
import json

# Get the input item once
input_data = _input.first().json
num_solutions = input_data['Number of solutions']
solutions_list = input_data['Solutions']

s = ""

for i in range(num_solutions):
    ai_output = solutions_list[i]

    clean_text = ai_output.strip()
    if clean_text.startswith("```"):
        clean_text = clean_text[7:]
    elif clean_text.startswith("```"):
        clean_text = clean_text[3:]
    if clean_text.endswith("```"):
        clean_text = clean_text[:-3]

    clean_text = clean_text.strip()

    try:
        data = json.loads(clean_text)
        s += "Idea number: " + str(i+1) + "\n"
        s += "Verdict: " + str(data.get("verdict_title", "N/A")) + "\n"
        s += "Recommended Sentence: " + str(data.get("recommended_sentence", "N/A")) + "\n"
        s += "Reasoning behind the verdict: " + str(data.get("reasoning", "N/A")) + "\n\n"
    except json.JSONDecodeError:
        s += "Idea number: " + str(i+1) + " (Error parsing JSON)\n\n"

return [{
    "json": {
        "formatted_output": s
    }
}]

